WEBVTT

00:02.370 --> 00:05.005
[ Ryan ]
This entire organization
is on stand-down...

00:05.039 --> 00:07.708
pending
an Article 32 investigation...

00:07.741 --> 00:11.179
for massive criminal action
and war crimes by members
of this command.

00:11.212 --> 00:15.649
My husband's a proud soldier,
but he's a poor excuse
for a man. He beats his wife!

00:15.683 --> 00:19.019
- Tell people whatever you want.
You explain this.
- What did you do?

00:19.053 --> 00:22.656
- Did you sign
the divorce petition yet?
- No.

00:22.690 --> 00:25.926
Would you do that, please?
I thought we could actually
save our marriage. I'll file it.

00:25.959 --> 00:30.030
What is this?
Your admission
to the stated charges.

00:30.064 --> 00:32.100
The Uniform Code of Military
Justice requires--

00:32.133 --> 00:35.569
[ Yelps, Yells ]

00:35.603 --> 00:39.107
We shut down the prisoner ship,
stopped the executions.
The Unit's being reinstated.

00:39.140 --> 00:41.609
- For now.
- For as long
as we hold the evidence.

00:51.419 --> 00:54.222
What you think, Sergeant?
Be ready by the end of the week?

00:54.255 --> 00:58.025
It takes that long, sir, you
need to fire me and get someone
in here who knows their job.

00:58.058 --> 01:02.396
All right, then,
I'll get out of your hair.
Have a good one.

01:02.430 --> 01:06.900
We can't possibly
finish that soon. This is
a two-week job at the least.

01:06.934 --> 01:09.036
You heard
what I told the colonel.
Yeah, but--

01:09.069 --> 01:13.574
We'll be up and in operation
by sundown tomorrow, or I'll
have your guts for garters.

01:23.917 --> 01:26.154
Hey, sweet thing.
What you got whuppin'?

01:26.187 --> 01:28.822
You, that's what's whuppin'.

01:28.856 --> 01:33.727
Facial spa
and a romantic night for two
at the Royal Arms?

01:33.761 --> 01:36.997
And who gave those
to you?
Found them in my coffee.

01:37.030 --> 01:42.069
Well, I will have
you know, madam, that
I'm a happily married man.

01:42.102 --> 01:46.907
Jonas,
it's a wonderful gift.
Why now?

01:46.940 --> 01:51.111
It's time we started eating
our desert first.
It surely is.

01:52.713 --> 01:55.849
[ Cell Phone Beeping ]

01:55.883 --> 01:58.452
Go for Blane.

01:59.720 --> 02:01.955
I hate that phone.

02:08.662 --> 02:10.631
[ Williams ]
Coffee's on the counter.

02:12.233 --> 02:14.168
[ Grunts, Sighs ]

02:14.202 --> 02:16.136
[ Williams Laughs ]

02:17.705 --> 02:21.842
Thanks for the loan
of the couch.
Long as you need it.

02:21.875 --> 02:25.112
First priority of the day
is gettin' my own hooch.

02:25.145 --> 02:28.616
- I heard there's a vacancy down
at that complex by the gate.
- [ Grey ] That place?

02:28.649 --> 02:32.353
Dude, it's full of lieutenants
and other small children.

02:32.386 --> 02:37.225
- Maybe they could use
a little... adult supervision.
- Like you could give it to 'em?

02:37.258 --> 02:41.028
- [ Chuckling ]
- Love to schmooze, dudes.

02:41.061 --> 02:45.466
I gotta pick up some stuff from
the house before I get a new
domicile. I'll catch you later.

02:45.499 --> 02:48.636
[ Door Closes ]
Don't forget to write.

02:48.669 --> 02:51.372
- Hey, Molly.
- You're staying after all.

02:51.405 --> 02:54.908
Yes, that's right.

02:54.942 --> 02:58.546
- I'm glad. I truly am.
- I gotta go, babe.
Hey, Mol.

02:58.579 --> 03:01.249
- Bob.
- You feelin' better?
Tummy calmed down?

03:01.282 --> 03:04.017
Well, I'll--
Nausea?

03:04.051 --> 03:07.355
Knocked up again.
You'd think she'd learn,
wouldn't you?

03:07.388 --> 03:11.892
- Can't you give
the poor woman a rest?
- Not with that face, no.

03:11.925 --> 03:15.162
- Barefoot and pregnant
wins the race.
- [ Truck Horn Honks ]

03:15.195 --> 03:18.031
Later, babe.

03:20.234 --> 03:23.537
And life returns
to its normal rounds.

03:23.571 --> 03:27.275
Looks like it.
It surely does.

03:29.443 --> 03:32.179
What ya doin', Dad?

03:32.212 --> 03:35.416
Your mom was supposed to leave
some things out for me.

03:35.449 --> 03:40.254
- What sort of things?
- Bedspread, towels, sheets.

03:40.288 --> 03:41.755
Dad?
Yeah.

03:42.890 --> 03:45.793
Why are you moving out?

03:52.433 --> 03:54.067
[ Slides Container
Across Floor ]
Come here.

03:56.437 --> 03:59.907
[ Sighs ]
Jen, darling,
I love you.

04:01.909 --> 04:06.547
I love your sister,
and I love your mom.

04:06.580 --> 04:09.317
And I always will.
Then stay.

04:13.354 --> 04:17.257
You know what?
This is just for a little while.
I'm gonna be back, and...

04:17.291 --> 04:20.961
this is kinda like the times
that I had to go before,
you know?
[ Door Opens ]

04:20.994 --> 04:23.831
Hey.

04:23.864 --> 04:26.334
- What are you all up to?
- Just gettin' some things.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.838
Hey, don't--
That's not nailed down.

04:30.871 --> 04:33.674
- Daddy!
[ Screaming ]
- [ Yelling ]

04:33.707 --> 04:35.809
Daddy!
Are you okay?
Get it off my leg!

04:35.843 --> 04:39.580
- Daddy! Are you okay?
- Tiffy!
Get it off my leg!

04:39.613 --> 04:41.782
All right.
You're caught.
[ Fabric Tearing ]

04:41.815 --> 04:44.418
Okay. Okay.
[ Jenny Screaming ]
Daddy!

04:44.452 --> 04:47.688
No! Help! My daddy's hurt!
No! Daddy!

04:47.721 --> 04:50.491
Somebody help!
[ Mack ]
It's okay.

04:50.524 --> 04:53.093
It's okay.
Gerhardts
are at it again.

04:53.126 --> 04:56.797
It's okay, it's okay.
It doesn't hurt.
It's just some scars.

04:56.830 --> 04:59.333
M.P.'s, I'm reporting
a domestic disturbance
in Belleau Wood.

04:59.367 --> 05:01.369
Yes, it sounds violent.

05:06.039 --> 05:09.042
[ Jonas ]
What do we know, sir?
Prelim info only.

05:09.076 --> 05:12.680
Pine Bluff Arsenal,
Arkansas, reports
a missing weapon.

05:12.713 --> 05:15.883
- Some old nerve agent bomb.
- A hell of a thing
to go missing.

05:15.916 --> 05:18.886
- I'm with you.
- It's the arsenal's job
to destroy those things.

05:18.919 --> 05:21.221
Stuff's been around forever,
some of it since
the Second World War.

05:21.254 --> 05:23.156
It could've got lost
in the shuffle.

05:23.190 --> 05:26.193
- Or worse.
- They have had accounting
and inventory glitches before.

05:26.226 --> 05:29.029
-That's right.
-Yeah, something gets misplaced,
winds up in the wrong bunker.

05:29.062 --> 05:31.965
We're the closest response
element available. We gotta
chopper down on pad now.

05:31.999 --> 05:34.802
You men hustle
down there and see
what you can make of this.

05:34.835 --> 05:36.570
Then we're away.

05:41.609 --> 05:43.411
Fare thee well.
[ Door Closes ]

05:45.846 --> 05:48.749
What are the rabbits for?
Canaries
in the mine shaft.

05:48.782 --> 05:52.352
Uh-huh.
And the rabbits?
That's what I mean. Same thing.

05:52.386 --> 05:54.588
They're much more sensitive
than any mechanical detector.

05:54.622 --> 05:58.058
At the faintest whiff
of agent, the rabbits die.

05:58.091 --> 06:00.828
- That's cold.
- They wanted a better job,
should've got their diploma.

06:00.861 --> 06:03.330
So how bad is this stuff?

06:03.363 --> 06:06.834
V.X. nerve agent
is the deadliest material
mankind has ever devised.

06:06.867 --> 06:09.102
The tiniest drop
on the skin
kills on contact.

06:09.136 --> 06:12.406
You blast it into a spray,
it becomes a--
a rain of death.

06:12.440 --> 06:15.743
- Then what sane person
would go near it?
- Exactly. No sane person would.

06:15.776 --> 06:17.745
That's what concerns me.

06:17.778 --> 06:19.747
Tracks show four men,
maybe five.

06:19.780 --> 06:23.417
Looks like they used a forklift
to get the thing on the truck
and simply drove away.

06:23.451 --> 06:26.053
Major, anything
on this truck?
A.P.B. with all police.

06:26.086 --> 06:29.757
- M.P.'s saw the truck drive
out the gate this morning.
- M.P.'s didn't stop it?

06:29.790 --> 06:32.025
Their orders are to check
vehicles coming in,
not going out.

06:32.059 --> 06:34.628
- Uh-huh.
- [ Chatter On Radio ]

06:34.662 --> 06:38.799
Sir, sheriff has
a fix on the truck.
Says a deputy has eyes on it.

06:38.832 --> 06:41.702
Tell them to seal the area
but do not approach.
No one in, no one out.

06:41.735 --> 06:44.271
Dr. Randall, no choice.
You're with me.

06:56.850 --> 07:00.420
- [ Deputy ]
Agent Greenbaum?
- Yeah. What you got, Deputy?

07:00.454 --> 07:03.491
Truck in question's parked
next to the hangar.
We've stayed back.

07:03.524 --> 07:05.493
Any movement?
None so far.

07:05.526 --> 07:08.529
- Any other way in here?
- No, sir.
But if you go around the--

07:09.697 --> 07:11.164
Hey!
Get down!

07:11.198 --> 07:13.100
[ Gunfire ]
[ Airplane Engine
Running ]

07:23.176 --> 07:25.879
- [ Bob ] Under the wing.
The nerve agent canister!
- [ Jonas ] Don't shoot it!

07:27.648 --> 07:29.950
[ Man ]
Man down! Officer down!

07:35.455 --> 07:38.058
Give him cover fire!

07:42.395 --> 07:44.498
- Want me to go with him?
- Go!

07:46.634 --> 07:48.736
[ Man ]
Reloading!

07:55.576 --> 07:57.511
[ Gunfire Continues ]

08:20.834 --> 08:24.504
[ Man ]
* Give me your secrets
Bring me a sign *

08:24.538 --> 08:28.375
* Give me a reason
to walk the fire *

08:28.408 --> 08:30.510
* See another dawn

08:30.544 --> 08:32.980
* Through a daughter's eyes

08:33.013 --> 08:36.416
* You give me a reason
to walk the fire **

08:59.106 --> 09:01.942
I don't care who's right.
I don't care who's wrong.

09:01.975 --> 09:04.511
But I do care about peace
and order within this command.

09:04.544 --> 09:07.114
Yes, sir.
Which command includes
on-base housing.

09:07.147 --> 09:09.783
Sergeant Gerhardt,
you will move
until further notice...

09:09.817 --> 09:12.052
into the bachelors'
N.C.O. quarters
where you will reside--

09:12.085 --> 09:14.354
Colonel, we weren't
even fighting.
Ma'am, the M.P.'s were called...

09:14.387 --> 09:16.256
to a domestic disturbance
in your home.

09:16.289 --> 09:18.792
It was not the first time.

09:18.826 --> 09:22.730
N.C.O. quarters where you will
reside until I have considered a
more permanent course of action.

09:22.763 --> 09:25.365
- Sir, I was moving today
to an apartment off-post.
- Rescinded.

09:25.398 --> 09:27.400
You will live in the B.E.Q.,
and you will not--

09:27.434 --> 09:30.270
you will not,
until I deign otherwise,

09:30.303 --> 09:33.073
be allowed in your house
unless accompanied by an escort
from this chain of command.

09:33.106 --> 09:35.075
Yes, sir.

09:35.108 --> 09:38.045
One more incident, and the
M.P.'s have to be called again,

09:38.078 --> 09:40.380
and, Ms. Gerhardt,
I will terminate
those quarters...

09:40.413 --> 09:43.150
and I will move you
and your children
out of that house...

09:43.183 --> 09:45.318
and off this base,
and, yes, I most certainly
can do that.

09:45.352 --> 09:48.622
Following which, Sergeant,
I will have you standing here
in front of this desk,

09:48.656 --> 09:51.659
at which time I will make
adjustments on your scorecard
on your permanent record.

09:53.193 --> 09:55.162
- Clear?
- Yes, sir.

09:55.195 --> 09:58.832
- Clear.
- [ Cell Phone Beeping ]

09:58.866 --> 10:03.270
This is Tom Ryan. Okay.
Roger that. Keep me advised.

10:03.303 --> 10:07.407
Mack, get down to the TOC. Kayla
will fill you in. Take charge
and make somethin' happen.

10:07.440 --> 10:10.978
I'll be with you
as soon as I can.
Yes, sir.

10:11.011 --> 10:14.314
Tom, if we could just talk,
I know that we could work it
so that--

10:14.347 --> 10:16.549
Good day,
Ms. Gerhardt.

10:18.385 --> 10:21.121
I need air sectionals
for the entire region.

10:21.154 --> 10:24.357
Put 'em up on the walls
and get me another phone line
in here immediately.

10:24.391 --> 10:26.960
Adelman, when's that commo net
comin' up?

10:26.994 --> 10:29.797
I think that--
[ Jonas On Radio ]
Snake Doctor, over!

10:29.830 --> 10:31.865
Snake Doc,
this is Dirt Diver. Go.

10:31.899 --> 10:37.004
- Take coordinates from location
of my transmission.
- [ Gunfire Continues On Radio ]

10:38.571 --> 10:40.473
Got it.
Done.

10:52.820 --> 10:57.024
Has left this location.
It is airborne in a--
What kind of plane?

10:57.057 --> 10:59.860
J-3, single-engine.
A single-engine J-3.

10:59.893 --> 11:03.997
Last seen heading...
north-northeast.

11:04.031 --> 11:05.866
Cool Breeze in pursuit.

11:07.434 --> 11:09.236
Make contact with him direct.

11:09.269 --> 11:12.740
Alert appropriate agencies.
Roger.

11:12.773 --> 11:18.311
We believe there are
at least four operatives,
maybe more.

11:18.345 --> 11:23.150
One in the plane.
We have at least two
that have us under fire.

11:23.183 --> 11:27.087
- Do you need assistance?
- Big time!
Send two additional teams.

11:27.120 --> 11:29.689
I'll alert those elements.
Anything else?
Yeah.

11:29.723 --> 11:32.392
Send a chemical
decontamination unit
immediately.

11:32.425 --> 11:35.763
- That's gonna take
a few hours, but wilco.
- Gotta go, Mack.

11:35.796 --> 11:38.698
- Busy day.
- Roger that.

11:39.733 --> 11:42.836
Doc, stay right where you are!

11:42.870 --> 11:45.672
I'm gonna maneuver behind.
Keep 'em engaged.

11:45.705 --> 11:48.441
Try not to get shot.
Copy that.

11:52.712 --> 11:54.915
[ Gunfire Continues ]

12:05.926 --> 12:08.095
Don't do it.

12:09.229 --> 12:11.231
[ Mutters ]

12:19.606 --> 12:21.541
All clear.
[ Man ]
All clear!

12:21.574 --> 12:25.278
Damn it.
I wanted one of 'em alive.

12:25.312 --> 12:28.816
Well, I wanted
that gunner out of action
before they killed us all.

12:28.849 --> 12:33.253
Can't always get what you want.
See if you can find anything on
'em might tell us who they are.

12:33.286 --> 12:35.622
- We'll turn 'em inside out.
- Get some pictures to the TOC.

12:35.655 --> 12:37.590
Maybe they can come up
with something.

12:37.624 --> 12:40.060
Hey, Doc!
Lend a hand.
[ Shutter Clicks ]

12:40.093 --> 12:43.130
You've seen these men before?
Maybe they worked
at the arsenal.

12:43.163 --> 12:45.765
- Betty Blue.
- Yo.

12:45.799 --> 12:48.168
See if the cruiser radio works.
Get some more police out here.

12:48.201 --> 12:50.470
I'm on it.

12:59.112 --> 13:01.581
I'm airborne,
about eight minutes behind,
following his initial heading.

13:01.614 --> 13:04.417
- You got eyes on him?
- No. No joy.

13:04.451 --> 13:07.587
[ Breaking Up ]
Air traffic control has nothing
on the radar in your area.

13:07.620 --> 13:09.857
Say again?

13:09.890 --> 13:14.427
Adelman, can we get
a clear channel over here?

13:14.461 --> 13:18.465
Barbarism.
That's what was done here--
pure barbarism.

13:18.498 --> 13:21.034
How's that, Cool Breeze?
Yeah, better.

13:21.068 --> 13:24.171
I said he must be flying
under radar coverage.
That's possible.

13:24.204 --> 13:27.340
- What's your altitude?
- Four and climbing.

13:32.245 --> 13:35.348
Hold what you've got.
Squawk your transponder.

13:35.382 --> 13:37.784
I'm gonna see
if control has you.

13:37.817 --> 13:40.287
Squawking... now.

13:40.320 --> 13:42.355
They've got you,
Cool Breeze,
but nothin' else.

13:42.389 --> 13:45.125
All right,
then he's below me.

13:45.158 --> 13:48.461
Look, I'm gonna fire wall
this thing and hold heading.
He can't be that far out.

13:48.495 --> 13:50.998
Roger that.
Is there anything
that I can do for you?

13:52.332 --> 13:54.167
Twenty knots more airspeed
would be nice.

13:54.201 --> 13:58.238
- I'll see what I can do.
Standing by this frequency.
- Roger, out.

14:00.540 --> 14:03.010
How long till we get
to minimum operational level--

14:03.043 --> 14:08.015
two secure radio links,
computer board working and
a direct line to the Pentagon?

14:08.048 --> 14:11.684
Colonel, this place was sacked.
The truth is, it may take days
to get what you want.

14:11.718 --> 14:14.187
You got 30 minutes.

14:17.090 --> 14:20.060
Don't look at me.
I was gonna give you
till tomorrow.

14:21.962 --> 14:26.033
Question of the century,
Mack: Where the hell
is this plane headed?

14:26.066 --> 14:29.136
A rendezvous with death.

14:30.237 --> 14:33.106
[ Tiffy ]
Your dad's gonna come visit you.

14:33.140 --> 14:36.176
He's gonna come see you
often as he can,
but there are rules.

14:36.209 --> 14:40.914
- What kind of rules?
- Darling, it just means that,
when your father is here,

14:40.948 --> 14:43.783
Jonas or someone else
from the Unit
will come with him.

14:43.816 --> 14:47.687
- So they won't fight--
is that it?
- And I'll come too. Both of us.

14:47.720 --> 14:51.524
- Is Daddy going away for good?
- No, darling.
We're gonna be all right.

14:51.558 --> 14:53.893
It's just gonna take
some getting used to,
that's all.

14:53.927 --> 14:57.064
But I don't want Daddy
to go away.
I want him.

14:57.097 --> 14:59.933
Oh, sweetheart.
Oh, baby.

14:59.967 --> 15:02.902
Grow up, Jen.
This is America.
Everybody's divorced.

15:02.936 --> 15:06.173
- It happens every day.
- Lissy--

15:07.640 --> 15:10.810
[ Sniffles,
Sobs ]
It'll be all right.

15:10.843 --> 15:14.481
It will.
It's gonna be all right.

15:14.514 --> 15:17.951
I'm telling you, this is
a can't-miss idea. It's being
done at radio stations...

15:17.985 --> 15:20.387
near Fort Bragg,
Fort Stewart,
Fort Benning.

15:20.420 --> 15:23.156
Okay, uh, call-in show,
army families.
Exactly.

15:23.190 --> 15:25.959
It's the single biggest
local demographic.

15:25.993 --> 15:28.295
Then why isn't
our crosstown rival
doin' it?

15:28.328 --> 15:32.132
Wh-Why were the Wright Brothers
the first to fly?
Why?

15:32.165 --> 15:37.337
Oh, come on, George.
You gotta know this can be done.
You gotta have the vision.

15:37.370 --> 15:39.906
Why do I gotta have
the vision?
You have the vision, George.

15:39.939 --> 15:42.075
You are a man of vision.
Am I?

15:42.109 --> 15:43.977
Everybody says so.

15:44.011 --> 15:46.613
What's the format?

15:46.646 --> 15:49.482
Present a current topic
of military life, one
of the perennial problems--

15:49.516 --> 15:52.619
It ain't like
there's a shortage--
then moderate a discussion.

15:52.652 --> 15:56.023
Like the lack of available
birth control.
If you will.

15:56.056 --> 15:58.658
What time of day?
Afternoon, before the kids
get home from school.

15:58.691 --> 16:01.094
We'll catch them at home
and at their workplaces.

16:01.128 --> 16:04.131
Who runs the show?
Me.

16:05.632 --> 16:07.600
I'm not the only one
who believes.

16:07.634 --> 16:10.337
I've got six
advertising spots
sold already.

16:11.704 --> 16:14.207
You have
six new advertisers
pre-sold?

16:14.241 --> 16:18.145
All locked up with two more
ready to sign tomorrow.
What do you say?

16:18.178 --> 16:21.781
Tell you what. You stick around,
punch the buttons
for the afternoon.

16:21.814 --> 16:23.016
We'll talk
when I get back.
This afternoon?

16:23.050 --> 16:24.717
When I get back.
So it's a go.

16:24.751 --> 16:27.287
Kim, I gotta go to the bank
for my monthly begging routine.

16:27.320 --> 16:31.191
And this here is the sort of
thing that's gonna keep you off
your knees and us on the air.

16:31.224 --> 16:34.327
We'll see.

16:34.361 --> 16:37.030
Dirt Diver,
Cool Breeze, over?

16:37.064 --> 16:39.299
Go, Cool Breeze.
I got nothing.

16:39.332 --> 16:42.202
Maybe the plane's
off on another heading.
Anything yet from air traffic?

16:42.235 --> 16:44.604
Negative.
Unless they put it down,
it's still under the radar.

16:46.206 --> 16:50.143
Wait a second.
I got a speck out front.

16:50.177 --> 16:53.546
Yeah, it's a plane about a--
well, I'd say at a heading
about a thousand feet below.

16:53.580 --> 16:56.116
I'm goin' in for a look.

17:02.555 --> 17:05.592
Just for a little while.
Doesn't have to be pretty.
It just has to work.

17:10.563 --> 17:13.500
Got him, Dirt Diver.
It's him.
Prepare to copy.

17:13.533 --> 17:17.437
Altitude, 1,500.
Airspeed, 100 knots.

17:17.470 --> 17:21.208
- Heading, 028 degrees magnetic.
- Good copy.

17:22.942 --> 17:25.412
Let me see if I can
force this guy to land.

17:25.445 --> 17:29.449
- With what?
- Well, persuasive argument.

17:48.335 --> 17:52.539
- I want to know already
where that plane's headed.
- [ Kayla ] It's 28 degrees mag.

17:52.572 --> 17:56.809
He's headed this way--
right smack towards
Fort Griffith.

17:58.611 --> 18:01.981
Dead rabbits.
They've been exposed
to the nerve gas.

18:04.016 --> 18:06.886
- Hey, Top,
you can't go in there alone.
- You two take charge out here.

18:06.919 --> 18:10.490
Set up a cordon, and
when the decon unit gets here,
make sure they're in place.

18:10.523 --> 18:13.393
If you don't hear from me,
just wait out here for help.

18:13.426 --> 18:16.095
Boss--
Do as I say.
That's an order.

18:16.129 --> 18:19.932
The rabbits are dead.
There's a great likelihood
the hangar is contaminated.

18:22.769 --> 18:24.036
[ Machine Gun Cocks ]

18:27.640 --> 18:30.443
[ Breathing Through Apparatus ]

19:10.250 --> 19:12.051
It gets worse.

19:12.084 --> 19:15.021
Dirt Diver,
Nobody's flying this thing.

19:15.054 --> 19:17.156
The pilot's dead.
Looks like nerve agent.

19:17.190 --> 19:20.860
Snake Doctor reported
nerve agent casualties
at his location.

19:20.893 --> 19:24.130
- Pilot could've been exposed.
- Well, he's liable to lose
his license for that.

19:24.163 --> 19:27.300
- It's no mistake.
- Cool Breeze, looks
like we know the target.

19:27.334 --> 19:31.137
Latest plot puts that thing
headed right here--
Fort Griffith.

19:31.170 --> 19:32.872
Good God almighty.

19:39.912 --> 19:43.216
[ Breathing Through Apparatus ]

19:59.566 --> 20:02.168
I got the data
on that type of weapon.

20:02.201 --> 20:05.938
-That thing makes it here,
it'll wipe out the entire area.
-You stay on this.

20:05.972 --> 20:09.776
How much time we got left?
No change in airspeed,
approximately 18 minutes.

20:09.809 --> 20:12.412
Adelman,
how many secure lines
we got working?

20:12.445 --> 20:14.881
One, and I'm sweet-talkin'
a second. Know in a few.

20:14.914 --> 20:18.851
Get me General Boldt on the horn
and then a continuous link
to National Command Authority.

20:18.885 --> 20:21.087
Can we shoot this thing down?

20:21.120 --> 20:23.556
Negative. If we detonate
the device midair, it'll
give a maximum dispersion.

20:23.590 --> 20:25.692
That's about
the worst thing
we could do.

20:25.725 --> 20:27.994
That makes our options
pretty damn slim.

20:44.344 --> 20:46.946
General Boldt,
sir.
Thank you.

20:46.979 --> 20:51.050
Sir, this is Tom Ryan.
We got a big problem.

20:51.083 --> 20:53.753
We have to evacuate the post.

20:53.786 --> 20:56.523
Yes, sir.
Deadly serious.

21:19.379 --> 21:21.748
- What's the status?
- Uh, Snake Doctor's
just entered the hangar.

21:21.781 --> 21:23.282
Alone?
Yeah.

21:23.316 --> 21:25.652
Well, you got contact with him?
Let's leave him alone.

21:25.685 --> 21:29.088
- If he needs help,
we'll hear it.
- Well, I don't like it,

21:29.121 --> 21:31.424
but I guess I don't have to.

21:31.458 --> 21:33.125
Look, photos
come in?
They're in the pipeline.

21:33.159 --> 21:35.595
Our computers are down,
but we're on it.

21:35.628 --> 21:38.465
Okay. Look, I got cops
pulling into the location.
I need to get back to you.

21:38.498 --> 21:40.933
Roger.

21:40.967 --> 21:43.169
[ Announcer ]
Playing all your favorites
without interruption.

21:43.202 --> 21:46.473
News and weather
at the top of the hour.
So keep that dial set...

21:46.506 --> 21:49.709
- to KTML, the Missile.
- [ Switches Off ]

21:49.742 --> 21:52.545
- Molly, thanks
for bringing them over.
- I'm glad to do it.

21:52.579 --> 21:56.349
You don't have to stay.
Teddy can sleep
and Serena can color.

21:56.383 --> 21:59.719
No way, girl.
Besides, I like
to watch you work.

21:59.752 --> 22:02.555
You're our personal
celebrity.

22:02.589 --> 22:06.559
- What's a celebrity?
- It's a famous person
like your mother.

22:06.593 --> 22:09.362
Oh.
Please. Being a deejay here
is nothing more...

22:09.396 --> 22:11.364
than being
a glorified button-pusher.
[ Phone Rings ]

22:11.398 --> 22:15.702
Now, I get my talk show,
you're gonna have to shoo
the tabloid photographers away.

22:15.735 --> 22:19.406
KTML Radio.
This is Kim Brown.

22:19.439 --> 22:22.909
Uh-huh.
"Severe weather,

22:22.942 --> 22:27.480
shelter,
mandatory alert."

22:27.514 --> 22:29.749
Yes, I've got it.

22:29.782 --> 22:31.584
Okay.

22:33.252 --> 22:35.221
[ Handset Settles
In Cradle ]
That was odd.

22:35.254 --> 22:39.358
What?
Call from Fort Griffith
Operations Center asking--

22:39.392 --> 22:42.729
no, demanding that we issue
a severe weather alert...

22:42.762 --> 22:46.899
and an "immediate shelter" order
for all personnel,
military and civilian.

22:46.933 --> 22:51.270
- Why is that odd?
- There's nothing on
the National Weather Service.

22:51.303 --> 22:55.007
- Is this some kind of a drill?
- Not if it pertains
to civilians.

22:55.041 --> 22:59.045
But it could be a crank call.
Think I should look up
the number to Base Ops,

22:59.078 --> 23:01.247
give 'em a call
and confirm?

23:01.280 --> 23:03.149
I know a better source.

23:11.991 --> 23:14.427
Molly Blane for Colonel Ryan.
It's important.

23:14.461 --> 23:18.264
Tom, I'm with Kim
at the radio station.
I'm calling--

23:18.297 --> 23:20.767
- Did you receive
the shelter notice?
- Colonel, we did. I just--

23:20.800 --> 23:23.803
Molly, may I speak
with Mrs. Brown?

23:25.738 --> 23:29.308
- Hello.
- Mrs. Brown,
I can verify that message.

23:29.341 --> 23:31.377
It is imperative
that you issue that alert.

23:31.410 --> 23:35.314
All personnel must take shelter
immediately and stay there
until further notice.

23:35.347 --> 23:38.217
- But, Colonel,
there's nothing on the--
- Kim, do you trust me?

23:38.250 --> 23:42.989
- Well, I--
- All personnel must
take shelter and stay there.

23:43.022 --> 23:46.959
- Am I cutting through?
- Colonel, the--
the alert will go out.

23:46.993 --> 23:48.761
I'll call you direct
with any more information.

23:52.198 --> 23:54.967
Kim?
I need to make
that announcement now.

23:55.001 --> 23:58.170
- Betty Blue, Snake Doctor.
- What gives, Top?

23:58.204 --> 24:00.973
- Relay all info
to the TOC.
- Right.

24:01.007 --> 24:03.242
I'm near the hangar
main door.

24:03.275 --> 24:06.145
One body, male,
possibly Eurasian.

24:06.178 --> 24:09.148
Will send photo.
No visible wounds.

24:09.181 --> 24:12.151
Foam around mouth, blue color
under the fingernails.

24:12.184 --> 24:16.088
Classic signs
of nerve agent poisoning.
The hangar must be contaminated.

24:16.122 --> 24:18.958
Doc says it's nerve agent.
Building's contaminated.

24:18.991 --> 24:22.294
I found one booby trap
and defused it,

24:22.328 --> 24:24.597
claymore on the wall.

24:24.631 --> 24:28.134
Hey, there's a claymore
over the door.
[ Jonas On Line ] Roger.

24:28.167 --> 24:33.840
There's a room at the far end,
the right as you enter.
I'll check it and report.

24:33.873 --> 24:39.011
Oh, yeah.
Check that photo of the body
against the Abu Said file.

24:39.045 --> 24:42.048
- Might be something there.
- Good copy.
I'll pass it on.

24:42.081 --> 24:44.016
Roger, out.

24:44.050 --> 24:47.219
Have you I.D.'d the bodies
in the photos?
What?

24:48.921 --> 24:50.990
I gotta get back to you.

24:51.023 --> 24:54.994
Adelman, they don't have
the photos, the ones that were
supposedly sent. Why not?

24:55.027 --> 24:57.229
- They were sent.
- But apparently not received.

24:57.263 --> 25:00.032
- Must be the interface.
- Buckwheat,

25:00.066 --> 25:03.302
the maximum effective range
of an excuse is zero meters.

25:03.335 --> 25:08.374
I expect results.
Get those photos sent
immediately. You got it?

25:09.742 --> 25:11.443
[ Quietly ]
Immediately.

25:13.245 --> 25:16.649
Pimple-headed paper pusher's
worried about pissants
in the pantry,

25:16.683 --> 25:21.253
we got...
elephants stampeding
through the wire.

25:21.287 --> 25:23.522
Cool Breeze,
this is Dirt Diver.

25:23.556 --> 25:27.760
Yes, ma'am. I can assure you,
I have the latest information.

25:27.794 --> 25:31.363
I know the Weather Channel
shows no storm clouds
approaching us,

25:31.397 --> 25:34.500
but this tornado warning
is the latest report.

25:34.533 --> 25:38.671
Ma'am--
Ma'am, please heed the warning
and stay undercover.

25:38.705 --> 25:41.608
Yes, ma'am, you can call back.

25:41.641 --> 25:44.343
Bye.
[ Sighs ]

25:44.376 --> 25:47.079
That's at least...
20 calls.

25:47.113 --> 25:51.417
I keep saying, "Take cover,"
but no other source
reports anything out there.

25:51.450 --> 25:55.387
Something's going on--
something military. What are
we gonna do with the kids?

25:55.421 --> 25:59.191
- Get them to a shelter.
- They need you. Just show me
which buttons to push.

25:59.225 --> 26:02.762
It's more complicated than that.
And-And-And I need
to warn other people.

26:02.795 --> 26:05.564
Molly, get my children
to safety.

26:05.598 --> 26:09.368
[ Mack ]
Dirt Diver, over.
Go, Diver.

26:09.401 --> 26:11.170
What the hell?
[ Engines Roaring ]

26:12.972 --> 26:16.075
Dirt Diver, I got air force
all over my ass!

26:17.576 --> 26:19.612
What are they doing?

26:19.646 --> 26:23.582
Rippin' through the wild blue.
Look, they can't go slow enough
to do anything,

26:23.616 --> 26:26.052
and if they fire a missile,
it'll blast that stuff
for miles around.

26:26.085 --> 26:28.888
Tell the flyboys to get
the hell out of there now.
What's the time?

26:28.921 --> 26:31.390
How much we got left?
How far out are we?

26:31.423 --> 26:34.060
Twelve miles,
five to the suburbs.

26:34.093 --> 26:37.096
We got everything
locked down here.
Everybody's undercover.

26:37.129 --> 26:39.966
But there's no cavalry
comin' to the rescue,
is there?

26:41.801 --> 26:45.104
You were air cav, right?

26:45.137 --> 26:48.307
It's just us, amigo,
and nothin' left to do
but hunker down and wait.

26:48.340 --> 26:51.844
Yeah, I hardly think so.
There's always somethin'
that can be done.

26:51.878 --> 26:54.513
This thing gets over the city,
it's a moot point.

26:55.614 --> 26:58.484
[ Engine Climbing ]

26:59.385 --> 27:01.387
Cool Breeze?

27:06.793 --> 27:09.228
Come in, Cool Breeze.

27:10.963 --> 27:13.332
Cool Breeze,
this is Dirt Diver, over!

27:27.046 --> 27:29.181
[ Engine Diving ]

27:31.650 --> 27:34.420
Cool Breeze,
this is Dirt Diver.
Don't do it.

27:36.055 --> 27:37.990
Cool Breeze, don't do it!

27:38.024 --> 27:41.593
- Bob, don't do it!
- Kiss my kids for me.

27:44.764 --> 27:49.035
Whoa! Dirt Diver--
Dirt Diver,
new heading, over!

27:50.569 --> 27:54.306
- Say that again, over.
- I say again, new heading:

27:54.340 --> 27:57.343
turned to 042 degrees
magnetic, over.

28:05.852 --> 28:09.756
- What happened?
- Plane's following
a programmed flight pattern.

28:09.789 --> 28:12.224
Must be on directed autopilot.

28:12.258 --> 28:14.660
[ Mack ]
That just bought us
a little time.

28:14.693 --> 28:16.863
Just bought me a lifetime.

28:16.896 --> 28:20.166
Yeah.
How's your fuel holding?
Uh, got several hours.

28:20.199 --> 28:23.936
I can't say the same
for my bladder though.
[ Laughs ]

28:23.970 --> 28:26.272
- Bitch and moan.
- It could be going to any one
of these cities.

28:28.207 --> 28:30.376
Just when you thought
it can't get worse.

28:33.712 --> 28:37.183
- Hey, Mack,
I'm thinking of somethin'.
- Always a good thing.

28:37.216 --> 28:40.252
Remember the tactic
the British fighter pilots used
on the German buzz bombs?

28:40.286 --> 28:43.189
I'm afraid I missed that war.

28:43.222 --> 28:47.226
You know what I'm talking about:
when they were trackin' a V-1,
and they were out of ammo?

28:47.259 --> 28:51.097
Yeah, I saw that documentary.
What are you,
a fighter ace now?

28:51.130 --> 28:55.434
Well, beneath me are miles
and miles of nothin'
but... miles and miles.

28:55.467 --> 28:59.171
- You want to give it
a shot, Red Baron?
- Here goes.

29:35.041 --> 29:38.677
- Nice and easy, okay?
- Who's flyin' this thing?

29:38.710 --> 29:41.647
Yeah, yeah.
Your radio goes out,
I'll know you didn't make it.

29:41.680 --> 29:44.283
What confidence.
Here goes.

29:54.827 --> 29:56.829
[ Breathing Heavily ]

30:29.761 --> 30:31.597
Whoa!
Turbulence.

30:54.520 --> 30:56.722
[ Phone Beeps ]

30:56.755 --> 30:59.992
Betty Blue,
have found a body in the office.

31:00.026 --> 31:03.395
Was holding a computer.
Maybe something there.

31:03.429 --> 31:05.231
Have cleared
for booby traps.

31:05.264 --> 31:07.199
I'm goin' in.

31:07.233 --> 31:10.202
Go easy and get out.

31:11.637 --> 31:13.639
Oh, yeah.

31:18.610 --> 31:20.779
[ Machinery Whirring, Snaps ]

31:22.982 --> 31:25.417
Well, that's special.

31:49.976 --> 31:53.645
- He's goin' down.
- You did it?
You took him down?

31:57.483 --> 32:01.020
Negative. Negative, autopilot
brought him back on course.
I'm gonna try it again.

32:26.045 --> 32:28.347
- Easy, Bobbo.
- Yes, Mother.

32:47.666 --> 32:49.901
No joy. No joy.
It's back on course.

32:52.304 --> 32:54.273
Damn.

32:54.306 --> 32:56.642
I've recovered
a laptop computer
from the body.

32:56.675 --> 33:00.379
- There might be
somethin' helpful there.
- Hope so.

33:03.849 --> 33:08.987
Pass this on: There was a trap
I didn't detect. It went off
as I entered the office.

33:09.021 --> 33:12.391
I've been sprayed
with a liquid--
some kind of gelatin.

33:12.424 --> 33:15.227
May I?

33:15.261 --> 33:17.963
- Do you have
a field test kit with you?
- Yes.

33:17.996 --> 33:20.399
Take out a piece of litmus paper
and touch it to the liquid.

33:31.177 --> 33:33.512
- Done.
- What color is it now?

33:33.545 --> 33:37.049
- It's black.
- Nerve agent.

33:37.083 --> 33:39.017
[ Jonas ]
Yeah, Doc,
I thought so.

33:39.051 --> 33:42.921
Look, once exposed,
how long is this suit
and mask good for?

33:42.954 --> 33:46.392
-How long before it breaks down?
-About two hours,
I should think, maximum.

33:46.425 --> 33:50.028
It's a layer of activated
charcoal in the suit
that provides your protection.

33:50.062 --> 33:55.867
As it degrades, the suit becomes
ineffective and... breaks down
more rapidly in the heat.

33:55.901 --> 33:57.103
Great.

33:59.471 --> 34:03.575
Testing. Testing.
Commo check, over?
Roger, out. Second head's up.

34:03.609 --> 34:07.012
What about that second
secure line?

34:07.045 --> 34:10.849
Finally got some info
on who this group may be.
Get this to Jonas.

34:10.882 --> 34:13.419
How's it lookin',
Mack?
I'm good, Colonel.

34:13.452 --> 34:16.855
Turned away from us,
passed our location.
Betty Blue, this is Dogpatch--

34:16.888 --> 34:20.726
Now the plane's making random
changes of heading. Any one
of these cities are in range.

34:20.759 --> 34:24.930
White House has been alerted.
But even if that air defense
artillery is en route,

34:24.963 --> 34:27.065
there's no guarantee
this thing can be stopped.

34:27.099 --> 34:29.468
Bob's the only one
that knows where it is.
That's the way...

34:29.501 --> 34:32.204
we've been able to plot it,
pass that information on
to command authority.

34:32.238 --> 34:36.742
We gotta bring this plane down.
Jonas is taking control
of the plane from that computer.

34:36.775 --> 34:40.446
He thinks that's
what's controllin' it.
God, I hope he's right.

34:40.479 --> 34:44.583
- Okay, I'm ready.
- I've made a code plan based
on the name of the group.

34:44.616 --> 34:48.287
Just punch in the keys
as I tell you.
We'll take it slow.
Okay.

34:48.320 --> 34:50.289
Ready.

34:50.322 --> 34:55.361
Pound, Zulu, One, Golf, Victor--

34:57.929 --> 35:01.600
- [ Bob ] I hope you've come up
with a solution back there.
- A lot of people are trying.

35:01.633 --> 35:03.835
Yeah, well, enough trying.
It's time for doing.

35:05.971 --> 35:08.106
New heading!
It's changed course again:

35:08.140 --> 35:10.842
046 degrees magnetic.

35:22.788 --> 35:24.490
Better not be.

35:27.793 --> 35:29.961
[ Grey ]
Echo, Romeo,
finally the dollar sign.

35:31.997 --> 35:34.500
- Got it.
- Okay, what do you got?

35:34.533 --> 35:37.369
Figures and coordinates.
The computer is not in control.

35:37.403 --> 35:39.471
The plane is on
a preplotted course.

35:39.505 --> 35:41.773
It's a self-guided missile,
but I know where it's going.

35:41.807 --> 35:45.177
All right.
Relay this to Dogpatch
as I call it out.

35:45.211 --> 35:47.379
Go ahead.
Location--

35:47.413 --> 35:53.118
West 900, 947.20.

35:53.151 --> 35:56.955
- Altitude, 1650--
- [ Vehicle Approaching ]

35:56.988 --> 35:59.057
A.G.L.

35:59.090 --> 36:02.127
Time: 1720 local.

36:02.160 --> 36:06.198
- Good copy. Great work.
- Good news. Decon team's here.
Betty Blue, out.

36:06.232 --> 36:10.001
Whoa.
Saint Louis.

36:14.506 --> 36:17.543
Cardinal Stadium.

36:17.576 --> 36:21.813
Baseball game.
Standing room only.
Jam-packed stadium,

36:21.847 --> 36:23.949
and it's rush hour.

36:37.263 --> 36:39.398
Well, at least now we know.

36:39.431 --> 36:41.099
- Yes, sir.
- Adelman,
get me Washington.

36:42.634 --> 36:45.170
Washington, now!

36:45.203 --> 36:47.739
They're going to gas
Saint Louis?

36:47.773 --> 36:49.441
Grab that man
by the stack and swivel!

36:49.475 --> 36:52.378
Which means,
it's no time to collapse.
[ Phone Rings ]

36:52.411 --> 36:55.581
- Everyone has to function.
Everyone!
- Right!

36:55.614 --> 36:58.384
Washington
on the line.

36:58.417 --> 37:01.287
- We all right?
You squared away?
- Yes, sir!

37:01.320 --> 37:04.423
- How about that cipher system?
Is it online yet?
- Most rikki-tik.

37:09.127 --> 37:11.297
Current winds
from the east
at six knots.

37:11.330 --> 37:15.301
Altitude of detonation, 1,650.
What's the stadium hold?
Call it 50,000.

37:15.334 --> 37:18.937
[ Mack Sighs ]
In the heart of downtown,

37:18.970 --> 37:21.773
we could be looking at--
[ Exhales ]
200,000 dead,

37:21.807 --> 37:25.210
who knows how many sick--
a half a million or more--
and Saint Louis uninhabitable.

37:25.243 --> 37:27.346
How much time we got?
What's left?

37:28.980 --> 37:31.783
- Speed the same?
- Yep.

37:31.817 --> 37:34.586
Twenty minutes to the suburbs.

37:34.620 --> 37:37.122
Well, Mack, you know
that just ain't
gonna happen.

37:37.155 --> 37:39.157
Yeah, I know.
The clock ran out on us.

37:45.130 --> 37:46.765
Can you patch me through to Kim?

37:49.134 --> 37:52.103
Adelman, you got
that land-to-line
communication set up?

37:52.137 --> 37:54.706
I don't have it yet.
I tried, but
I don't have it.

37:59.778 --> 38:03.315
I can't make that happen,
Cool Breeze. Is there a message
you want me to pass on to her?

38:04.616 --> 38:07.252
You make it up.
You know what to say.

38:07.285 --> 38:08.954
[ Quietly ]
Yeah.

38:14.059 --> 38:18.096
White House has issued
the button-down order.
It'll help, but not much.

38:18.129 --> 38:21.132
Well, at least they can have
response teams poised
outside the city.

38:21.166 --> 38:23.335
Hey, what happens
when a plane stalls?

38:26.372 --> 38:28.073
What happens
when a plane stalls?

38:30.542 --> 38:32.944
It loses all lift.

38:32.978 --> 38:38.216
It stops flying. I-It, uh--
It goes into a spin
and crashes.

38:38.249 --> 38:41.353
And an autopilot can't pull
out of a stall, can it?
It takes a pilot--

38:41.387 --> 38:43.355
a real live one--
to counter a spin.

38:43.389 --> 38:46.725
Yeah, that's right.
It takes a pilot.
It takes a live one.

38:51.597 --> 38:55.634
All right, look.
There's a large open field
up ahead.

38:55.667 --> 38:57.736
Take my coordinates
and notify Emergency Response.

38:57.769 --> 39:00.238
Wilco. What the hell
you got planned,
Cool Breeze?

39:00.271 --> 39:02.441
Stop jabberin'
and leave me alone.

39:40.278 --> 39:42.414
[ Engine Diving ]

39:50.889 --> 39:53.792
[ Bob Straining ]

40:25.791 --> 40:28.560
Splashdown.
No detonation.

40:28.594 --> 40:32.564
- Yeah!
- He did it. He did it!

40:32.598 --> 40:34.833
He did it!
[ Laughs ]

40:34.866 --> 40:37.202
There will be
no living with him now.
[ Laughs ]

40:46.512 --> 40:48.514
[ Laughing ]

40:54.119 --> 40:56.555
[ Man ]
Can you raise your arms
for me, please?

40:59.157 --> 41:01.493
A little higher.

41:04.162 --> 41:06.798
Can you turn around?

41:06.832 --> 41:09.434
And that's the latest news
from KTML.
** [ Rock On Speaker ]

41:09.467 --> 41:13.371
And to all our listeners
in the Greenwood-Fort Griffith
area,

41:13.404 --> 41:17.509
that severe weather notice
posted earlier today
has been called off.

41:17.543 --> 41:21.713
And the winner of the $500 pool
for when the order
would be rescinded...

41:21.747 --> 41:25.183
goes to Mrs. Lynn Edwards
of Renfro.

41:27.152 --> 41:32.457
We hope you weren't
inconvenienced, but, hey,
better safe than sorry.

41:32.490 --> 41:35.994
And now back to more
of your favorite music
here at KTML, the Missile.

41:36.027 --> 41:38.196
** [ Switches To Low Volume ]

41:38.229 --> 41:40.265
[ Exhales Deeply ]

41:45.737 --> 41:48.006
- [ Door Opens ]
- Kim!

41:48.039 --> 41:51.309
- Am I fired?
- [ Scoffs ] Fired?
Fired nothin'. You were great.

41:51.342 --> 41:54.746
But the callers--
they were beating me
from left to right.

41:54.780 --> 41:57.649
So what? You kept them engaged.
And more than that,
you kept your head.

41:57.683 --> 41:59.885
You really know how to handle
a tough situation.

41:59.918 --> 42:02.721
And turnin' the whole thing
into a contest? Brilliant.

42:02.754 --> 42:07.525
After what you did
this afternoon, a regular
call-in show is a piece of cake.

42:07.559 --> 42:10.428
You mean the show?
I got the show?

42:10.461 --> 42:15.366
Until you get fired.
[ Chuckles ]
Don't screw it up.

42:15.400 --> 42:18.704
[ Rock Continues ]
* And, baby, my liberty

42:20.872 --> 42:24.209
I don't know whether
to wash with this
or drink it.

42:24.242 --> 42:27.278
That suit was at its limit.
I don't think it would've lasted
another half hour.

42:27.312 --> 42:30.849
- Oh, well.
- A harrowing experience, but
I've learned so much today.

42:30.882 --> 42:33.885
Well, ain't that special?
No, but it will be.

42:33.919 --> 42:37.022
I intend to use this incident
to scare the pure hell
out of Congress...

42:37.055 --> 42:39.557
and get the money
to finish destroying
these bioweapons.

42:39.591 --> 42:43.962
Well, good luck
with that, Doc.
Thank you.

42:43.995 --> 42:47.065
Ah, Mr. Blue,
would you hand me a towel?

42:47.098 --> 42:50.769
* I ain't got no reason to wait
Gonna lose my mind *

42:50.802 --> 42:54.139
* Never hesitate
And would you mind
givin' me my pants?

42:54.172 --> 42:57.643
More than you know.

42:57.676 --> 43:01.046
* Singin', here comes the time
of the revelation *

43:01.079 --> 43:04.082
* Get a one-way ticket
for your salvation **

43:05.283 --> 43:07.686
** [ Fades ]

43:30.275 --> 43:33.111
[ Door Opens ]

43:34.179 --> 43:36.281
[ Exhales ]

43:36.314 --> 43:37.983
[ Door Closes ]

43:45.056 --> 43:47.325
- Got our bags packed?
- [ Chuckles ]

43:49.327 --> 43:50.896
[ Murmurs Quietly ]

43:53.364 --> 43:56.167
[ T.V. Announcer ]
And that's one out here in
the bottom of the eighth inning.

43:56.201 --> 43:58.804
Score's still tied
at 4-4 with runners--

43:58.837 --> 44:02.140
Okay, so with-- with runners
on first and second,
if there's less than two outs,

44:02.173 --> 44:04.509
then the infield fly rule
is in effect.

44:04.542 --> 44:06.978
- Oh, a little popcorn.
- [ Announcer Continues ]

44:07.012 --> 44:09.214
Daddy's telling me about
the infield fly rule.

44:09.247 --> 44:11.683
And?
I think
he's making it up.

44:11.717 --> 44:15.821
I thought you didn't care much
for baseball.
Hmm.

44:15.854 --> 44:20.458
Today, it's
my second favorite pastime.
And delivers, fastball--

44:20.491 --> 44:22.694
[ Bat Hits Ball ]
There's the drive...
deep into right center field!

44:22.728 --> 44:25.797
Reece Bradley has done it!
That is outta here!

44:25.831 --> 44:30.736
Home run! And just like that,
Saint Louis jumps ahead, 7-4--
